NOTES:
This file demonstrates the HOLD feature using `=` symbol.

SECTION 1 - BASIC HOLD (8 beats):
  Beat 1: Fret 7 on e string (+ B,G strings chord) - START
  Beat 2: HOLD (all 3 strings continue)
  Beat 3: HOLD (all 3 strings continue)
  → Total duration: 3 beats
  
  Beat 4: Fret 5 on e string - START
  Beat 5: Fret 3 on e+B+G - START
  Beat 6: HOLD (B+G continue)
  → Fret 3 duration: 2 beats

SECTION 2 - HOLD WITH TECHNIQUES (8 beats):
  Beat 1: Bend 1 step at fret 7 - START
  Beat 2-3: HOLD bend (keep bending)
  → Bend duration: 3 beats
  
  Beat 4: Hammer 5→7 + chord - START
  Beat 5: HOLD (chord continues)
  → Chord duration: 2 beats
  
  Beat 6: Fret 3
  Beat 7-8: Rest

SECTION 3 - MIXED HOLD LENGTHS (8 beats):
  Beat 1: Fret 7 (e+B) - 2 beats duration
  Beat 3: Fret 5 (e) - 4 beats duration!
         (B continues from beat 1)
  Beat 7: Fret 3

DISPLAY BEHAVIOR:
- Active note highlights for FULL duration
- Tech line shows only at beat START
- Hold beats don't create new steps

LEGEND:
Hold Symbol:
  =     = Hold previous note (1 beat extension)
  ==    = Same as = (formatting)
  ===   = Same as = (formatting)
  ====  = Same as = (formatting)

All `=` variations mean: "Extend previous note by 1 beat"
Use any number of `=` to match your TAB width formatting.

Examples:
  |7|=|=|     → Fret 7 plays for 3 beats
  |7|==|===|  → Same: Fret 7 plays for 3 beats
  |7b{1}|=|=| → Bend plays for 3 beats
